## Toolchain Standardization

### Dev Container (devcontainer.json)
Standardize the entire dev environment in a container — everyone has the same JDK, tools, and extensions:

```json
{
  "name": "Java 21 Dev Environment",
  "image": "mcr.microsoft.com/devcontainers/java:21",
  "features": {
    "ghcr.io/devcontainers/features/docker-in-docker:2": {},
    "ghcr.io/devcontainers/features/kubectl-helm-minikube:1": {}
  },
  "customizations": {
    "vscode": {
      "extensions": [
        "vmware.vscode-spring-boot",
        "redhat.java",
        "ms-azuretools.vscode-docker"
      ],
      "settings": {
        "java.configuration.runtimes": [{"name": "JavaSE-21"}]
      }
    }
  },
  "postCreateCommand": "mvn dependency:go-offline -q",
  "forwardPorts": [8080, 5432]
}
```

Result: new developer opens repo in VS Code → click 'Reopen in Container' → fully configured environment in minutes, no manual setup.
